ences";a:69:{i:0;s:41:"What Is the Meaning of Chairman Emeritus.";i:1;s:109:"The organization only gives the Chairman Emeritus title to someone it still values as a member of the family.";i:2;s:69:"Because it is mostly a ceremonial position there is no extra pay for.";i:3;s:97:"Chair Emeritus means the Chair Emeritus of the Board of Trustees elected pursuant to Section 435.";i:4;s:21:"Based on 1 documents.";i:5;s:80:"Chair Emeritus means the former Chair who most recently served in that position.";i:6;s:93:"A Chairman Emeritus is somebody who has retired from the Chairmans position in good standing.";i:7;s:88:"The people who are considered Emeriti have no official position on a board of directors.";i:8;s:93:"However they may be called upon by the Chairman or the board in general for special purposes.";i:9;s:171:"Chairman Emeritus means the past Chairman of the Company who shall be appointed as Chairman Emeritus by the Board of Directors subject to the approval of the shareholders.";i:10;s:38:"What is the meaning of chair emeritus.";i:11;s:38:"A chair emeritus is an honorary title.";i:12;s:93:"It is given to someone who has officially retired from their position but retains their rank.";i:13;s:85:"A chairman emeritus has retired from his position but retains his professional title.";i:14;s:142:"As an honorary title an emeritus position involves few if any responsibilities but the individual retains a relationship with the institution.";i:15;s:47:"Emeritus is a Latin word for earned or merited.";i:16;s:101:"Chairman Emeritus is an honorary position usually given to people who have retired from the position.";i:17;s:40:"It is just a respect to person named so.";i:18;s:148:"Chairman Emeritus is like a head of family who lost all powers to younger generation but have high regards at least in society if not in the family.";i:19;s:16:"Time for a quiz.";i:20;s:301:"A way to get dead wood out the door without creating an enormous stink a way to honor a founder who no longer can or wants to be involved in the organization he or she created a way to keep big-money people giving without having to listen to their opinions retired or honorably discharged from active.";i:21;s:13:"Entry 1 of 2.";i:22;s:118:"A person retired from professional life but permitted to retain as an honorary title the rank of the last office held.";i:23;s:38:"Definition of emeritus Entry 2 of 2 1.";i:24;s:97:"Holding after retirement an honorary title corresponding to that held last during active service.";i:25;s:190:"The title emeritus is often given to important people who previously headed an organization or department are now retired but are still involved with the organization in some meaningful way.";i:26;s:113:"You may have seen or heard titles such as pastor emeritus professor emeritus chair emeritus or director emeritus.";i:27;s:194:"As in the USA the title of professor emeritus may be awarded to a retired or former professor who may well retain formal or informal links with the institution where the chair was formerly held.";i:28;s:108:"Many professorships are named in honour of a distinguished person or after the person who endowed the chair.";i:29;s:25:"What is a chair emeritus.";i:30;s:144:"When you see someone introduced as a companys Chairman Emeritus it means youre looking at a person who once worked as Chairman of that business.";i:31;s:70:"The term Emeritus signifies the person still enjoys a similar rank to.";i:32;s:47:"Emeritus means they no longer work with you eg.";i:33;s:75:"They are retired but continue to have a relationship with the organization.";i:34;s:47:"Deceased persons are no longer emeritusemerita.";i:35;s:113:"When organizations want to remember deceased individuals they list the years of service not the years they lived.";i:36;s:113:"Retired or honorably discharged from active professional duty but retaining the title of ones office or position.";i:37;s:37:"Dean emeritus of the graduate school.";i:38;s:25:"Editor in chief emeritus.